SIMPLE: unpack
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Unpack
<hw>Un*pack"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[1st pref.
<ets>un-</ets> + <ets>pack</ets>.]</ety>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>1.</sn> <def>To separate and remove, as things packed; to open
and remove the contents of; <as>as, to <ex>unpack</ex> a
trunk</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To relieve of a pack or burden.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Shak.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Unpacker</ent>⟦br⟧
